In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reports on the recent attacks by militia groups affiliated with Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) against United States personnel and facilities in Iraq and Syria. In response to these attacks and ongoing threats, the United States conducted targeted strikes against facilities in eastern Syria used by the IRGC and affiliated groups. The strikes were carried out to reaffirm deterrence, protect US personnel, degrade ongoing attacks, and deter future attacks. President Biden directed these actions in accordance with his responsibility to protect US citizens and national security interests, as well as his constitutional authority as Commander in Chief. The military action was conducted in compliance with international law and the inherent right of self-defense. The President assures that the United States is prepared to take further action if necessary and provides this report to keep Congress informed, in line with the War Powers Resolution.